{
  "texts": [
    "Although inferred transition probabilities are predominantly used for more in-depth data analyses based on estimators, we also provide means to visualize cellular dynamics directly based on the kernel output.",
    "These visualizations are intended to provide a preliminary understanding of the underlying dynamics and serve as a starting point for further analyses.",
    "Here, we enable studying the evolution of cellular state change either based on random walks in the high-dimensional gene expression space or a projection of the high-dimensional vector field onto a low-dimensional latent space representation of the data.",
    "Transition matrices induce random walks modeling the evolution of individual cells.",
    "Given a cell j, we successively sample its future state k under the given transition matrix."
  ]
}